  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bca\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0ba3\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd - \u0bb2\u0b95\u0bcd\u0bb7\u0bcd\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Some have retreated from general conformity - Laxman Kiriella",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Although an initial consensus was reached between the opposition parties on the prime ministerial candidate of the interim government, some parties have now backed away from that position. That is why the Speaker did not announce the name of the new Prime Minister on Friday the 15th, MP Lakshman Kiriella said.",
        "He said this at a press conference held on Friday 15th at the office of the Leader of the Opposition in Colombo, while he further mentioned,",
        "The United People's Power has been trying since the beginning to form an all-party government with the consensus of all party leaders.",
        "However, only 62 members of Parliament will support us. Also, our position was that one from the opposition party and one from the ruling party should be appointed to the two main positions in the government.",
        "But the current government does not want that. Instead, the All-Party Government was formed by buying off members of other parties. However, it was decided in the meeting held on 15th to propose the name of Opposition leader Sajith Premadasa as the Prime Minister for the government to be formed next week.",
        "Therefore, today (yesterday) we informed the Speaker that the name of the new Prime Minister will be announced. However, in the meeting held with the opposition again today (yesterday), only a few have backed away from that position. That is why he did not announce the decision on the new Prime Minister to the Speaker.",
        "Field Marshal Sarath Fonseka, the United People's Shakti leader, is a person we all respect. However, we have no position regarding his announcement. He said that he should be asked about it."
      ],
